items.title: Indian carriers refuse regulator’s data request in brewing tiff
items.description: The airlines have instead suggested they only share airfare data on a percentage of tickets sold in the future and only in specific cases, not as a routine practice, the letter said

items.title: Centre says quashing Volkswagen's $1.4 billion tax bill would be 'catastrophic'
items.description: India’s highest-ever demand for back taxes related to import duties came after scrutiny of 12 years of Volkswagen shipments and has rekindled foreign investors’ fears over lengthy investigations.
